[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm wondering why dynamic coverage isn't detecting executed APIs while Jacoco does. Maybe dynamic coverage only considers native runs, not JVM? It’s possible native executions weren't run after our recent changes. I should inspect the class report HTML to see if there's anything interesting.
[thinking] 
[thinking] If the dynamic coverage relies on metadata generated by the agent, it might not include certain executions. Perhaps the user-code filter is excluding some classes, which could complicate coverage matching. It really seems like reflection and class coordination could be contributing to these coverage issues.
